A taxi driver is lucky to have escaped a crash uninjured on a gravel road in Mvutshini on the South Coast, recently.Netcare 911 media liaison officer, Shawn Herbst, said, “Reports from the scene indicated that the driver of a mini-bus taxi lost control resulting in the vehicle leaving the road above a Bilanhlolo low level bridge, landing upside down.Medics assessed the scene and found that the adult male driver was the only occupant in the vehicle. The patient, however, who escaped injury declined ambulance transportation to hospital.”